dcterms:description: A grid-world maze environment where the agent needs to reach the goal zone in the bottom-right corner, moving one square in any of the four directions (north, south, east, west). The agent receives a reward of -0.004 for each time step and 1 for entering the goal zone.
dcterms:title: Grid-World Maze

dcterms:description: A reinforcement learning environment where the goal is to keep a pole balanced by moving a cart forward and backward for 200 steps. The agent receives a reward for maintaining balance.
dcterms:title: CartPole

dcterms:description: A collection of various video games used as environments for testing reinforcement learning algorithms, particularly in the context of maximum-entropy reinforcement learning.
dcterms:title: Atari Games
